sentences: Harold Boyd Elder (January 12, 1944 – October 6, 2018), also known as "El Chingadero", was an American artist.
Elder is best known for creating the painted skulls used in the cover artwork for The Eagles' 1975 album One of These Nights and their compilation album Their Greatest Hits (1971–1975).

In April 1972, Elder exhibited his latest works in an art gallery in Venice, California, in a solo show titled "El Chingadero" (meaning "The Fucker").
However, on May 31, 1973, his studio burnt down including 15 pieces of the artwork that he had planned to exhibit.
